  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "System Engineer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><strong>Engineering & Design</strong></p><ul><li><p>Design system architecture in accordance with project specifications, drawings, and authority requirements</p></li><li><p>Prepare control schematics, network layouts, IO lists, panel layouts, and technical submissions</p></li><li><p>Develop functional design specifications and control logic</p></li><li><p>Select appropriate controllers, servers, and field devices</p></li></ul><p><strong>Programming & Configuration</strong></p><ul><li><p>Configure and program controllers, servers, and field devices</p></li><li><p>Develop system graphics, alarms, trends, and reports</p></li><li><p>Integrate third-party systems using open protocols (e.g., BACnet, Modbus, TCP/IP, OPC)</p></li><li><p>Maintain system backups and configuration records</p></li></ul><p><strong>Testing & Commissioning</strong></p><ul><li><p>Conduct factory and site acceptance tests (FAT/SAT)</p></li><li><p>Perform point-to-point checks, loop testing, and system verification</p></li><li><p>Commission systems and support client handover</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues during commissioning</p></li></ul><p><strong>Project & Site Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Coordinate with project managers, site teams, subcontractors, and vendors</p></li><li><p>Attend technical meetings with clients, consultants, and authorities</p></li><li><p>Support site installation works and ensure compliance with approved drawings</p></li><li><p>Prepare as-built drawings and final documentation</p></li></ul><p><strong>Maintenance & Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide technical support during the defects liability period</p></li><li><p>Attend system faults, perform root cause analysis, and recommend corrective actions</p></li><li><p>Support system upgrades, modifications, and optimization</p></li></ul>",
